  "aiHints": {
    "analysisContext": "MJPEG = sequence of JPEG frames. Raw MJPEG: consecutive JPEG frames (FFD8...FFD9 blocks). AVI MJPEG: RIFF/AVI with MJPG FourCC in strf biCompression, frames in movi as 00dc chunks. IP camera MJPEG: HTTP multipart/x-mixed-replace stream (MIME boundaries between frames). Each JPEG frame: SOI(FFD8) + segments (FFC0/SOF0 contains width/height at bytes 5-8: 2B height BE + 2B width BE) + SOS(FFDA) + compressed data + EOI(FFD9). MJPEG quality: quantization tables in FFDB segment. DRI(FFDD) segment sets restart interval.",
    "suggestedInspections": [
      "Verify 0xFF 0xD8 at offset 0 — JPEG SOI",
      "Bytes 2-3: segment marker. 0xFFE0 = JFIF, 0xFFDB = quantization table (camera MJPEG)",
      "Find SOF0 (0xFFC0) segment: bytes +5/+7 = height/width (BE uint16)",
      "Count SOI (0xFFD8) occurrences to estimate frame count in raw MJPEG stream"
    ]
  },
